				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Anyone been banned from using the Air pet on raids because you get blamed for the tank not being able to keep argo on a monster?  Some people in my guild are blaming the argo generated by an air pet for the main tank not being able to position a monster.  They have even gone so far as to think about banning all pets on raids.  WHile I can understand why they would do this.. We have way too many people that instantly send a pet in and then go afk, both of which are bad... 
<br />

<br />
  Has anyone else ever been asked about this and is it a normal thing that the air pet can steal argo away from the Main tank.. not by actually stealing argo and getting hit instead of the MT, but instead of having the monster switch to your pet when the MT tries walking away to get the monster in a better position.
<br />

<br />
 BTW, I search the boards, more then 9 pages in and couldn't find anything on this. Sorry if it has been asked before and I didn't see it.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
