			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Easy way to see if the pets are getting aggro is to /assist the mob. 
<br />

<br />
The way our raids are disciplined, basically everyone knows who has aggro at all times (meaning what the mob thinks). The only times I have ever seen pets getting aggro are situations like:
<br />

<br />
* Mob self-memblurs and pet happens to be mid-swing or mid-taunt. Pet may get aggro for a second or two before MT regains
<br />

<br />
* Mob fears MT and other PCs off. Pets (at high levels) appear to be fear-immune, so they are the only ones left meleeing. You usually die shortly after your pet does in these situations <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="Sad" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=568700" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
