			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I use air pet on every mob i can, unless its a mob i know will be cornerd then i use water.  If your ma is loosing aggro to a pet then its time to either a) fire the slacker or b) get him some better gear.  In south ldon there is a stun proc mod for wpns that works good for those who dont have a better wpn.  The aggro mod on the BOW is a godsend for casters.
<br />
     But as it has beet stated before, pets cannot get aggro over players.  All the aggro from the pet goes to the closest pc.  So how is your pet even getting aggro over the ma?  If the critter is getting to far away from the melle, are the other melle on your raids not trying to be on the oposite side of the ma? If so then its not the pets fault, its your melee being lazy and hitting auto attack and just following the critter around.
<br />
Mayby its time for raid 101 for some people.<br />_________________<br />dmuerte
<br />
cranky mage of Rodcetnife
