Pets can get aggro over melees, however the mob will always hit the PC with the highest aggro if they are in melee range. You can check if the pet has more aggro than the PC - have player back up. If the mob turns on the pet instead of following the PC - the pet had more aggro.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>chaosmage wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Some people in my guild are blaming the argo generated by an air pet for the main tank not being able to position a monster.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
This quote makes me think that your guild MIGHT be right. Try using the water pet with taunting off for a while and see what happens.
<br />

<br />
Also, don't send your pet in before the ASSIST call is made (or until the bulk of your other melees engage). This will keep your pet from getting early aggro and let the main tank properly position the mob first.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=99869" target="_blank">Perelandra Eldil - Arch Convoker</a> 
<br />
Gelil - Oracle
<br />
Druzzil Ro</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
