				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>chaosmage wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">But my point is this.  Unless your ma is just hitting autoattack and going afk he should never be out of range of the critter.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
During positioning, the MT get's initial aggro and the back's up to move the mob where he wants it. When he back's up - he is out of range (on purpose) so that the mob will follow him. If your pet is taking aggro, the mob turns around and smacks the pet instead of following the tank. This is bad.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=99869" target="_blank">Perelandra Eldil - Arch Convoker</a> 
