			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As someone who plays both a mage and a warrior, I can say that what  we have here is a failure to communicate.
<br />

<br />
Item 1)  Aggro is a ladder.  Pet aggro HELPS a warrior overall, because his taunt puts him at MAXHATE+1.  If a pet actually has more aggro, a successful taunt will put tank back on top.  This helps him stay ahead of casters.  Pet taunt helps this also.
<br />

<br />
Item 2) The tank needs to communicate when he's moving a mob.  He needs a hotkey that says "Moving %t:  back off pets", and he needs to use it before he starts moving the mob, and then he needs to hit taunt before he backs away.
<br />

<br />
Item 3) The tank should NOT spam the taunt key.  He should have it available, and use it every time wizzy_01 slams the mob for a 4k shot, or the mob turns and pops the rogue/ranger/DT_magnet_01.
<br />

<br />
Item 4) Do not jump assist.  Wait for it. (Yes, sometimes this means a pre-occupied warrior will solo tank the whole fight.  He asked for it.) 
<br />

<br />
Item 5) Pet classes that hit /pet attack and go afk:  well, that is what /guildremove is for.  8(<br />_________________<br />Banda Gemaker
<br />
Human Mage of 65 Summonings
<br />

<br />
Dalanaf Silvermine
<br />
Dwarven Warrior of 47 Summers
<br />

<br />
Ulfga Silvermine
<br />
Barbarian Shaman of 51 Winters
<br />

<br />
Meyoole Skeener
<br />
Elven Bard of the 47th Song</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
