			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Several good points so far. Anyways... Water Pet is great for raids, especially AoW style mobs since you get their back. /taunt off is required but if the MT stays in melee range its no big deal. If anything your pet will get owned on rampage mobs. On mobs that do rampage you need to let the tank teams set the rampage first.
<br />

<br />
Now pets can be used for positioning if done right. You MUST wait for the MT to engage and you most position your pet so it can push. In this case pets are useful. I also use HoE for this purpose as well. Those little craplings are great for moving a mob, but you have to do it right. I use this tatic on Rallos/Fake Rallos, all AoW style fire mobs, EarthB mobs, etc... It took a while to break the old no pets habit on raids from back in the day, but if you use them right they are a great advantage.<br />_________________<br />Mordican - Arch Mage of Infinite Visions
<br />
Maelin Starphyre Server
<br />

<br />
"The Stupid... You have to admire their consistancey"</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
